sentences: In 2004, Mack released his first album, Average Guy.
The first single, "We Can't All Be From Texas," reached the top 10 on the Texas Music Chart and was used by George W. Bush during his 2004 election campaign.
It was also played in the stadium during the stadium of the 2004 college football game between Oklahoma Sooners and the University of Texas Longorns (the Red River Shootout.)
It was released in July 2007 in Canada on Open Road Recordings.
Mack released his third album, The Journey, in 2009.
In 2012, Mack formed the group Friday Night Satellites.
